Document: Material
Path: godot/classes/class_material.rst
Summary: Base class for all material types in Godot, defining properties and methods common to shaders.

Inherits: Resource < RefCounted

The Material class is the base class for all material types in Godot. Materials are used to define the surface properties of objects, controlling how they interact with light and how they are rendered. This includes properties like color, texture, shininess, transparency, and more. All materials in Godot inherit from this base class, ensuring a consistent interface for accessing and manipulating material properties.

Materials are typically assigned to the `material` property of a `MeshInstance` or other visual nodes. They are also used in conjunction with `ShaderMaterial` to apply custom shader code.

Key Rule: Materials are resources, meaning they can be saved, loaded, and shared across multiple objects. This allows for efficient memory usage and easy management of visual assets.
